The Senate on Wednesday urged the President, Major General Muhammad Buhari (retd.), to expedite actions on the prosecution of sponsors of the Boko Haram sect.  The Senate Committee on Army made the request at a press conference it addressed shortly after the Chief of Army Staff, Lt. Gen. Tukur Buratai, led other generals to defend the 2021 budget of the Army, behind closed doors Chairman of the committee Senator Ali Ndume, who spoke on behalf of his colleagues, said Buhari should emulate the leadership of the United Arab Emirates which recently prosecuted and jailed some identified sponsors of the deadly sect. Details later… Source Immediate past Nigeria’s Chief of Army Staff, General Onyeabor Azubuike Ihejirika has replied former Minister of FCT, Mallam Nasir El Rufai on his allegation that the former army general was one of the chief sponsors of the Boko Haram sect. The former army boss said El Rufail is one of… August 28, 2014 In "News" Former minister of aviation, Chief Femi Fani-kayode has described as despicable, allegation by Australian negotiator, Stephen Davies that former Army Chief, Azubuike Ihejirika was one of the sponsors of the terrorist Boko Haram sect. The Perth-based Davis who was involved in negotiations on behalf of the federal government with commanders… August 30, 2014 In "News" SOKOTO - Prof. Shehu Riskuwa, Former VC Usman Danfodio University, Sokoto, on Saturday expressed confidence that the present administration would weed out Boko Haram insurgency. Riskuwa told the News Agency of Nigeria ( NAN ) in Sokoto that President Muhammadu Buhari, being an army general, would come out with stringent… May 30, 2015 In "News"